history.content:
I don't think 188 fits. It's mostly useful for those who want to do research on rl (which is about machine playing games and robotics control and is different from other data driven ml).

EE126 workload is higher than 170 from my perspective and an average student in 126 is more competitive than 170 since 126 is very "specialized" for people who do ml research. 

PS: Both prob 140 and ee126 are good preparation for cs189, but taking both is extremely redundant with a high overlap in material.
